{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But we didn't do it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it was-- even on that day when the roundup was there, when we were all caught and cordoned off, that morning, still, this [NON-ENGLISH] below us-- she was a widow on her own.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Particularly, she liked Eve.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She offered to hide us in her house there that day, but my parents wouldn't do it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Anyway, she was always very good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we got back to Maastricht, we, we contacted this [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she came to Maastricht, and she collected Eve.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Eve went with her to Amsterdam and stayed there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went to the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after a few days, we were let out of the camp, when they sorted out that we were all right.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were sent to a Jewish orphanage in Laren, not far from Naarden, where we had lived at one time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and it was a Jewish orphanage with lots of other survivors and people and children who'd been in hiding and children in general of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Meanwhile, Eve was in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in Laren, we started to go back to school again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, I went to the same school that I had started in Bussum.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After Naarden, I'd started another school in Bussum, a higher-- lyceum, a higher education school, and I went back to that same school in Bussum in 1945.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In the meantime, we contacted all the-- my parents' friends, and we got all our things back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in particular, we contacted our aunt in Palestine and the uncle in London.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the uncle in London, particularly, he had found out about us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had been searching the lists, and all that sort of thing, and they heard we'd survived.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
